                     <interp inst="t18290115-230-defend1789" type="age" value="24"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             were indicted for <rs id="t18290115-230-off1235" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290115-230-off1235" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-230-off1235" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18290115-230-cd1236" type="crimeDate">12th of January</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-230-off1235 t18290115-230-cd1236"></join>, 1 coat, value 5s.
            </rs>, the goods of a person unknown.</p>

               <p>JOB BRANCH. I am a gardener, and live at Maida-hill, Paddington. On the 12th of January I was in Lisson-grove, and met the two prisoners in company - they crossed the New-road and went down Stigo-lane; they then turned into Upper York-street, and went about forty yards to the left - there was a gig at the door of No.39; they crossed, looked into it, and went on towards Seymour-place- they appeared to speak to each other; Lindsey went up to the gig on the driving side, and took out a drab great coat - he turned the corner of Windham-place, and Green followed him; he threw the coat on his back, and they went on through several streets to George-street, Portman-square, Langham-place, Regent-street, and then turned into Oxford-street - as they went along they continued to look at the coat and to admire it; I met several patrols in Oxford-street - I spoke to them; Cost ran, and got ahead of them - they then cut across the road; I stopped them and said,</p>
               <p>"You must not go any further" -Cost then came up and said,</p>
               <p>"Where did you get that coat?" Lindsey said,</p>

               <p>"I bought it; I can tell you where, but I shall not" - the coat belonged to a visitor, who is gone into the country.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. What are you? A. A florist; my garden is at Maida-vale-I went to the house the next morning; the proprietor said it was a gentleman who called, and he knew nothing of him - the coat was taken between five and six o'clock in the evening; they were taken about half-past six - I never prosecuted a person before in my life; the prisoners did nothing to me - I have no prejudice against them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-230-person1790">
                  GEORGE 
                  Cost
               <interp inst="t18290115-230-person1790" type="surname" value="Cost"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-230-person1790" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-230-person1790" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Bow-street patrol. I was on duty - Branch told me some persons had stolen a coat; I asked where it was, and he said they had got it on - I crossed the road, and they crossed; I returned, and took them into custody - I asked Lindsey where he got it; he said he had bought it - I took them to the office, and went in search of the owner; I found the house, but could not find him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did you search them? A. My brother officer did; there were 13s. and a watch found on them.</p>
               <p>LINDSEY'S Defence. I was coming down the square, and met an elderly man dressed like a countryman who asked for relief; he had this coat, which he said he could not pawn and would sell it to me for 5s. - I put it on; it fitted me, and I gave him 5s. for it; I met this young man, and told him I had bought a coat - he was looking at it when these men came and took me.</p>
               <p>GREEN'S Defence. I met this prisoner; he said he bought the coat - we were walking home.</p>
               <p>GREEN - <rs id="t18290115-230-verdict1237" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290115-230-verdict1237" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 22.</p>
               <p>LINDSEY - <rs id="t18290115-230-verdict1238" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290115-230-verdict1238" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 24.</p>
